&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT HUT 8&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine the ultimate destination for those who want to work at the cutting edge of technology, &lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;energy,&lt;/span&gt; and infrastructure. Hut&amp;nbsp;8 is on a mission to build and operate some of the world’s largest data centers for next-generation computing workloads, including AI, Colocation, Cloud, and Bitcoin Mining. We are proud to offer interesting and challenging opportunities for individuals who want to build teams, solve problems, and make an impact from day one. If you’re an ambitious individual looking for a career that is as rewarding as it is challenging, you’ve come to the right place.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly analytical and intellectually curious Business Intelligence professional to serve as the dedicated BI partner for Corporate SG&amp;amp;A functions at Hut 8. This role sits within the Business Intelligence organization and partners directly with functional department leaders to move those teams from data delivery to decision-enabling insight.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Associate will be expected to go beyond reporting what the data says. The standard for this role is to surface insight, recommend a course of action, and articulate the expected outcome — equipping leadership with clear, decision-ready intelligence across cost drivers, headcount, vendor spend, and operational efficiency. This role is expected to leverage AI tools and modern analytics platforms to build always-on intelligence, not static reports.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;SG&amp;amp;A Performance Monitoring &amp;amp; Variance Analysis&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze actual spend against approved budgets across all Corporate SG&amp;amp;A cost domains, identifying and articulating key variance drivers across people costs, professional services, technology, and T&amp;amp;E.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain forward-looking cost forecasts, including reforecast cycles, that translate variance trends into a recommended view on full-year outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build interactive dashboards that surface cost trends proactively, reducing reliance on manual report generation and enabling faster decision cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Decision-Ready Insight Delivery&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate data findings into a clear narrative: a starting point, a realistic range, and a defensible recommendation – not just a summary of what happened.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with department leaders to understand their operating context and ensure BI outputs are calibrated to their actual decision needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the cadence of regular reporting for assigned SG&amp;amp;A functions, including monthly performance packages and ad hoc analysis in support of leadership decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Process Improvement, Tooling &amp;amp; Standardization&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop standardized reporting frameworks and forecasting templates across assigned SG&amp;amp;A cost domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and share tooling and process improvements across the BI team to build organizational leverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or related field. Advanced degree preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in business intelligence, FP&amp;amp;A, or corporate finance, with meaningful exposure to SG&amp;amp;A cost structures and functional department partnering.&lt;/li&gt;
