&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Energy Subject Matter Expert:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You possess deep knowledge of the North American power grid, including interconnection, transmission and distribution approval processes, and complex tariff structures.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You will have deep familiarity procuring power in both regulated utility markets and competitive retail energy markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Negotiator:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You have a proven track record of lead-negotiating multi-party infrastructure deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Risk Manager:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You can identify and mitigate regulatory and operational dependencies—such as curtailment risks and upgrade obligations—before they impact project delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integrated Advisor:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You excel at serving as an energy subject-matter expert for cross-functional teams in Strategic Transactions, Finance, and Development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive negotiations for interconnection agreements, shared facilities and other co-tenancy agreements, transmission service agreements, distribution arrangements and other utility infrastructure agreements;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate and structure power supply agreements, energy service agreements, retail energy supply agreements and ancillary service arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide legal analysis of various utility tariffs and rate structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to speed on key policies impacting generation procurement, interconnection policies, transmission and distribution policies and regulations impacting power procurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the power-related portions of project financing deliverables, including diligence requirements and lender covenants.&lt;/li&gt;
