&lt;p&gt;Imagine the ultimate destination for those who want to work at the cutting edge of technology, &lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;energy,&lt;/span&gt; and infrastructure. Hut&amp;nbsp;8 is on a mission to build and operate some of the world’s largest data centers for next-generation computing workloads, including AI, Colocation, Cloud, and Bitcoin Mining. We are proud to offer interesting and challenging opportunities for individuals who want to build teams, solve problems, and make an impact from day one. If you’re an ambitious individual looking for a career that is as rewarding as it is challenging, you’ve come to the right place.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Associate General Counsel, Strategic Transactions to serve as the lead legal partner for the company’s most significant strategic and transactional initiatives. In this high-impact role, you will lead the legal execution of mergers and acquisitions, joint ventures, strategic partnerships, project financings, and other complex corporate transactions that are central to the company’s long-term growth strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with executive leadership and cross-functional teams to structure, negotiate, and execute sophisticated transactions across a rapidly evolving infrastructure platform operating at the intersection of energy, AI infrastructure, and digital assets. This role offers substantial exposure to strategic decision-making, financing initiatives, and enterprise-level legal and business issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong transactional and financing experience with practical business judgment, a high degree of ownership and autonomy, and the ability to operate effectively in a fast-paced, execution-oriented environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deal Execution Lead: You have significant experience leading complex M&amp;amp;A transactions, joint ventures, strategic investments, and other high-value corporate transactions from structuring through closing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finance &amp;amp; Transaction Structuring: You have experience supporting sophisticated financing transactions, including acquisition financings, structured debt arrangements, project financings, or other capital markets and infrastructure-related transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Problem Solver: You are capable of navigating complex commercial, regulatory, and structural issues and developing practical, business-oriented solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Operator: You work effectively across legal, finance, tax, treasury, development, and executive teams and are comfortable coordinating multiple stakeholders under demanding timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independent and Commercially Minded: You are comfortable operating independently, managing multiple high-priority matters simultaneously, and exercising sound judgment in dynamic environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead legal support for mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, joint ventures, strategic partnerships, minority investments, and other strategic transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all phases of transaction execution, including structuring, diligence, negotiation, documentation, financing coordination, closing, and integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support transaction-related financing activities, including acquisition financings, project financings, debt facilities, and related covenant and diligence matters.&lt;/li&gt;
