&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT HUT 8&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine the ultimate destination for those who want to work at the cutting edge of technology, &lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;energy,&lt;/span&gt; and infrastructure. Hut&amp;nbsp;8 is on a mission to build and operate some of the world’s largest data centers for next-generation computing workloads, including AI, Colocation, Cloud, and Bitcoin Mining. We are proud to offer interesting and challenging opportunities for individuals who want to build teams, solve problems, and make an impact from day one. If you’re an ambitious individual looking for a career that is as rewarding as it is challenging, you’ve come to the right place.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate, Strategic Finance, you will play a central role in executing the financing and capital markets activities that fund the company&#39;s infrastructure growth and long-term financial strategy. Working alongside senior members of the Strategic Finance team, you will structure and evaluate capital solutions, build the analysis behind key decisions, and support transactions from concept through close — an ideal foundation for an ambitious finance professional in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will gain hands-on exposure to high-impact financing transactions, liquidity and capital planning, and the strategic decisions that shape the company&#39;s capital structure. You will work closely with senior leadership and regularly engage with banks, investors, and capital partners, contributing directly to outcomes as part of a small, fast-moving team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the key responsibilities you should expect are the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Financing Initiatives:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Help identify, structure, and evaluate financing solutions to fund infrastructure investments, client contracts, and continued growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Modeling &amp;amp; Analysis:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Lead financial modeling efforts to&amp;nbsp;assist senior finance team in analyzing opportunities and strategic decision making across equity, debt, lease, and hybrid capital solutions, including debt capacity, leverage, liquidity, covenant sensitivity, and downside scenarios.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capital Markets Support:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Conduct market research across capital-markets trends, investor appetite, peer benchmarking, and emerging financing structures, and support the execution of capital raising and financing transactions, including evaluation of key financing terms, drafting presentations, and assisting with management of key lender and financial sponsor relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Contribute to high-visibility, cross-functional special projects that move the business forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Recommendations:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Contribute to the preparation of recommendations for firmwide investment committee on financing strategies, M&amp;amp;A opportunities, and new investment opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transaction Execution &amp;amp; Coordination:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Support deal workstreams from launch through close — including data room management, diligence responses, and documentation coordination — and partner with legal, accounting, energy origination, tax, and corporate development teams to keep assumptions and deliverables aligned, maintaining a financing pipeline view across projects, counterparties, and key milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
