&lt;div class=&quot;textLayer&quot; data-main-rotation=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THIS ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
The Digital Delivery Manager is the strategic owner of how Hut 8 creates, coordinates, and governs digital project data across its growing portfolio of data center and energy infrastructure programs. This role goes beyond traditional BIM management — it encompasses the full digital delivery lifecycle, from model creation and clash coordination through asset naming governance, CMMS planning, and digital twin strategy. Operating at the intersection of construction technology and operational readiness, the Digital Delivery Manager ensures that every digital artifact produced during design and construction is accurate, standards-compliant, and structured to serve the organization long after project handover.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;p-pdf_iframe__page&quot; data-page-number=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Develop and enforce Hut 8’s BIM Execution Plan (BEP), establishing enterprise-wide standards for model creation, file structures, naming conventions, and data interoperability across all active and future projects&lt;br&gt;• Own the configuration and governance of Autodesk Construction Cloud — managing user permissions, submittal workflows, model publishing protocols, and issue tracking to ensure a disciplined, auditable digital environment&lt;br&gt;• Build and maintain Hut 8’s digital delivery framework, defining how project data is created, coordinated, reviewed, and handed over across internal teams and external partners including EPC contractors and design consultants&lt;br&gt;• Lead clash detection and model coordination efforts, identifying and resolving spatial conflicts across architectural, structural, mechanical, electrical, and plumbing disciplines before they impact field execution&lt;br&gt;• Drive CMMS planning and asset data integration strategies, ensuring that digital models and asset naming conventions are structured to transition seamlessly from construction tools to operational maintenance systems at project handover&lt;br&gt;• Align document and asset naming standards across all digital delivery platforms in coordination with the Document Control function, enforcing consistency across SharePoint, ACC, and downstream systems&lt;br&gt;• Evaluate and integrate emerging digital delivery technologies — including digital twins, CFD&lt;br&gt;modeling, reality capture, and AI-assisted coordination tools — recommending strategic adoptions that advance Hut 8’s competitive position&lt;br&gt;• Deliver tailored training programs to internal stakeholders and external partners, building organizational fluency in BIM tools, ACC workflows, and digital delivery standards&lt;br&gt;• Conduct regular audits and quality assurance reviews of BIM models and datasets to maintain accuracy, completeness, and adherence to project and enterprise standards&lt;br&gt;• And other duties as assigned
